From c2d277c9b8fe517d73c735f7e0720179beff1a04 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vincenzo Grimaldi <vince.ceccarelli@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 16:01:24 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(responsive): full mobile/viewport alignment + pulsating
 chatbot launcher

Responsive fixes (every breakpoint 320px and up):
- Hero h1 now scales text-4xl -> sm:5xl -> md:6xl -> lg:7xl; subhead
  and all large headings/CTAs given proper mobile steps
- Fixed hero divider w-[900px] -> w-full max-w-[900px] (horizontal
  overflow source on phones)
- Chat panel was fixed 380x560px and overflowed small phones; now
  w-[calc(100vw-2rem)] max-w-[380px], h-[min(560px,100dvh-7.5rem)] --
  fits every device height including keyboard-open states
- Footer columns collapse 2 -> sm:3 -> lg:5 instead of jumping to 5 at md
- Utility bar tightened for narrow screens; Product Preview link hidden
  below sm to prevent crowding
- Pricing page display numbers scale down on mobile
- prefers-reduced-motion respected for all new animation

Chatbot launcher:
- Icon changed MessageCircle -> Bot (on-brand for a robotics company)
- Soothing dual-ring pulse: two staggered expanding rings (3.2s,
  Intercom-style) + gentle breathe scale on the button; pulse pauses
  while the panel is open; fully disabled under reduced-motion
- Launcher repositioned bottom-5 right-5 on mobile, bottom-8 right-8 desktop

Honesty: removed leftover fabricated promise in chat footer
('real responses in < 2 min') -> scripted-demo disclaimer
